children.subject:
Mastering the probability part of CS 70 will help you only during the first 2 weeks of 126. 

If I were you, I'd make sure to master CS 70 probability and then start reading 126 textbook and do some of its problems. Good thing is Ramachandran is teaching, so you are in a good hand.

history.content:
I'm a return student coming in next semester which is why I'm asking this mid-semester.

I took 70 SP19 and forgot most if not all of the material there, especially since I didn't really need to use those concepts much outside of that class. My understanding is the concepts in 70 are reviewed in the first few weeks of the class and then move on to new stuff from there. 

I'm wondering if it would be better to really master the concepts in 70 again assuming they're all foundational to the later concepts in 126 or if a survey of the course material would be better preparation for the class. Any and all advice would be appreciated!
history.subject: Best way to prepare for EECS 126?
